cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

The paper discusses a technique for deriving statements about functions based on their types, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL). The technique involves deriving quantitative theorems, which involves logical reasoning (cs.LO). The paper also discusses examples of applying the technique to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper focuses on short-cut fusion, which is a technique for optimizing functional programs (cs.FL).
